crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a member of the Crysis (Dharma) ransomware family. It utilizes dynamic API resolution (sub_4065e0) to evade static detection and contains internal implementations of cryptographic algorithms, including SHA-1 (sub_405f30) and AES-like block ciphers (sub_403ae0, sub_4034c0), for file encryption. The binary enumerates local drives (sub_409780, sub_409ee0) and network shares (sub_4078d0) to maximize its impact. The presence of the PDB path 'C:\crysis\Release\PDB\payload.pdb' is a high-confidence indicator for attribution to the Crysis malware strain.
